{
  "texts": [
    "Even if the GDPR does not define \"legal effects,\" the Guidelines on Automated Individual Decision-making and Profiling from WP29 (hereafter, \"Guidelines\") clarify that the automated decision must affect someone's legal rights, legal status, or their rights under a contract.",
    "31 See extensively TERESA QUINTEL, DATA PROTECTION, MIGRATION AND BORDER CONTROL: THE GDPR, THE LAW ENFORCEMENT DIRECTIVE AND BEYOND (2022).",
    "28 Bygrave, supra note 18, at 532.",
    "29 Consiglio di Stato [Italian Higher Administrative Court], Case No. 2270/2019, (Apr.",
    "8, 2019), https://www.medialaws.eu/ wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Consiglio-di-Stato-sez.-VI-8-aprile-2019-n.-2270.pdf (last accessed Feb. 27, 2024)."
  ]
}